2.1.8.2 New-style Multi-Line Strings
....................................

The combination of вҺ•INP for immediate execution mode and multi-line
strings for defined functions achieved, at least in principle, the goal
of specifying large amounts of text in a simpler manner than in standard
APL. However, having different methods for creating multi-line string
literals in different APL modes could not convince entirely.

   The search for a more intuitive and more consistent solution then led
to new-style multi-line strings.  These strings adopted the triple quote
(""") syntax known from e.g.  the Python language.  The syntax of
new-style multi-line strings is cleaner: empty lines are handled more
consistently and the string lines are completely separated from the APL
code lines.  More importantly, new-style multi-line strings work alike
in immediate execution mode, in scripts, and in defined functions.
New-style strings are a little different and syntactically stricter than
their old-style companions:

   вҖў the starting """ must be placed at the end of an APL code line,
     i.e.  there is no more mixing of APL code and string content in the
     same line.  An old-style string starts with APL code and ends with
     the first line of the string, while a new-style string starts with
     an APL code line and the string itself begins at the following
     line.

   вҖў the ending """ must be placed at the end of a separate line with
     only spaces allowed before the """ (to horizontally indent-align it
     with the leading """ if so desired).  In old-style strings the text
     up to the termination " is part of the string while in new-style
     strings it is not.

   вҖў Neither the starting nor the ending line become nested strings of
     the result, and every line can be clearly identified as being
     either APL code or else string text.

   Example:
      4 вҺ•CR """
     ABC
      DEF

       GHIJK
            """
     в”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”“
     в”ғв”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”“ в”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”“ в”ҸвҠ–в”“ в”ҸвҶ’в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”“в”ғ
     в”ғв”ғABCв”ғ в”ғ DEFв”ғ в”ғ в”ғ в”ғ  GHIJKв”ғв”ғ
     в”ғв”—в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣ в”—в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣ в”—в”Ғв”ӣ в”—в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣв”ғ
     в”—вҲҠв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣ

   When entering new-style multi-line strings, the prompt is prefixed by
вҶ’ to indicate that a Multi-Line String is being entered.

   вҺ•INP and old-style strings will coexist for a while, but may
eventually disappear at some point in time.


