2.1.8.3 В« В» Strings
...................

When new-style multi-line strings are used in scripts the related error
reporting (if the syntax is used incorrectly) can become cumbersome.
For example, if one forgets the closing """ of a multi-line string then
the next """ (which was meant as the start of a new multi-line string)
is mistaken as the (forgotten) end of the previous one.  The often long
content of the new string is then parsed as APL code and will usually
produce many error messages, all of them nonsense.  Things get worse if
the script itself is long because the odd/even nature of the quotes will
then persist until the end of the string (or at least until the next
forgotten quote, if any).

   To deal with this problem, GNU APL also allows strings whose contents
are enclosed in double angle quotation marks В« and В».  In inline strings
вҖҷ...вҖҷ and "...", as well as in multi-line strings """ ...  """, there is
no general (and reliable) way to decide if a user has forgotten the
ending quote(s), which leads to the problems above.

   For this reason, GNU APL now also allows inline and multi-line
strings like, for example:

           В«Hello worldВ»
     Hello world

           8 вҺ•CR В«В«В«
     вҶ’      Line 1
     вҶ’        Line 2
     вҶ’      В»В»В»
     в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
     в”Ӯв”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җв”Ӯ
     в”Ӯв”ӮLine 1в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  Line 2в”Ӯв”Ӯ
     в”Ӯв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳв”Ӯ
     в””Пөв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ

           вҚқ provoke an error...
           вҚқ
           8 вҺ•CR В«В«В«
     вҶ’      Line 1
     вҶ’         Line 2
     вҶ’            В«В«В«

     *** WARNING: unexpected triplet В«В«В« in mult-line string.
         Expected triplet: В»В»В» (literal depth: 0).
         The triplet was added to the multi-line string.

     вҶ’            В»В»В»
     в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
     в”Ӯв”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җв”Ӯ
     в”Ӯв”ӮLine 1в”Ӯ в”Ӯ   Line 2в”Ӯ в”Ӯ      В«В«В«в”Ӯв”Ӯ
     в”Ӯв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳв”Ӯ
     в””Пөв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ

   Another advantage of В«В«В« ...  В»В»В» over """ ...  """  is that a decent
text editor (read: vi/vim) may jump back and forth between the opening В«
and the corresponding closing В» with a single key stroke (character % in
vi/vim).  For this to work, add the following line to /etc/vim/vimrc (or
to ~/.vimrc):

     set matchpairs+=В«:В»


