2.1.8.4 Multi-Line Comments
...........................

One of the badly missing features of standard APL are comments that span
multiple lines.  However, in GNU APL one can use multi-line strings in
combination with monadic primitive вҠЈ for that purpose:

           вҠЈВ«В«В« вҚқвҚқвҚқ
            Multi-line
            Comment
            ...
            В»В»В» вҚқвҚқвҚқ

   The triplet вҚқвҚқвҚқ in the example above is optional and has no effect
(since it is part of the multi-line string, but is then suppressed by
вҠЈ), but is nevertheless recommended as an indication that the text
between the вҚқвҚқвҚқ is a comment.

   GNU APL is aware of this construct and optimizes it away entirely.
Therefore even long multi-line comments inside loops have, like normal
APL comments, no performance penalty at runtime.


