   Argument KPAD also shows the keypad of the keyboard.  The keypad is
normally hidden so that the output fits into a 80-column terminal
window.  With KPAD the terminal should have at least 101 columns.  The
standard GNU APL layout puts line graphics characters onto the keypad,
as well as В« and В» and some currency symbols.

   Argument FUNK also shows the function key row of the keyboard, but
only for ]KEYB XMOD KEYS:

           ]KEYB XMOD KEYS FUNK KPAD
