2.20 Bit-wise Logical Functions вҠӨвҲ§, вҠӨвҲЁ, вҠӨвҚІ, вҠӨвҚұ, вҠӨвү , and вҠӨ=
==========================================================

The APL functions And (вҲ§), Or (вҲЁ), Nand (вҚІ), and Nor (вҚұ) operate
primarily on Boolean integers.  Primarily means that the LCM variant for
вҲ§ and the GCD variant for вҲЁ are not considered in this context.  (The
LCM and GCD variants are defined in the ISO standard and supported in
GNU APL but not in IBM APL2).

   However, probably more often than not one needs to compute Boolean
functions between the bits of arbitrary (non-Boolean) integers and not
between entire Boolean integers 0 or 1.  Although that is possible to do
in standard APL, the procedure is fairly awkward and, more importantly,
inefficient:

   вҖў convert every integer argument X to a 64-item Boolean vector
     XвҶҗ(64вҚҙ2)вҠӨX,
   вҖў call the Boolean function вҲ§, вҲЁ, вҚІ, вҚұ, =, or вү  with the converted
     arguments, and
   вҖў convert the Boolean result vector R back to the integer result
     ZвҶҗ2вҠҘR

   Note: for Boolean arguments the APL functions вү  and = can be used to
compute the more customary Boolean functions XOR and XNOR respectively.
In this context = and вү  are treated as Boolean functions even though
they accept non-Boolean arguments,

   For example, using 5 вҺ•CR (4вҚҙ256)вҠӨX to display X in hex:

           5 вҺ•CR (4вҚҙ256)вҠӨ   AвҶҗ$ABBADEAD
     ABBADEAD
           5 вҺ•CR (4вҚҙ256)вҠӨ   BвҶҗ$00FF00FF
     00FF00FF

           5 вҺ•CR (4вҚҙ256)вҠӨ   2вҠҘ ((64вҚҙ2)вҠӨA) вҲ§ (64вҚҙ2)вҠӨB
     00BA00AD

   With the bit-wise And (вҠӨвҲ§) the same can be achieved in a simpler
fashion and far more efficiently:

           вҚқ Traditional AND
           5 вҺ•CR (4вҚҙ256)вҠӨ   AвҶҗ$ABBADEAD
     ABBADEAD
           5 вҺ•CR (4вҚҙ256)вҠӨ   BвҶҗ$00FF00FF
     00FF00FF

           вҚқ bit-wise AND
           5 вҺ•CR (4вҚҙ256)вҠӨ   A вҠӨвҲ§ B
     00BA00AD

