2.24 вҺ•CC - Character Classes
============================

Some older APL interpreters (e.g.  APL68000) had system variables for
character classes, such as вҺ•D for digits 0..9 or вҺ•A for letters A..Z.
GNU APL provides a single system function вҺ•CC for that purpose.

* Menu:

* monadic вҺ•CC B: Return character class::
* dyadic A вҺ•CC B: Test character class::


File: apl.info,  Node: monadic вҺ•CC B: Return character class,  Next: dyadic A вҺ•CC B: Test character class,  Up: вҺ•CC - Character Classes

2.24.1 monadic вҺ•CC B: Return character class
--------------------------------------------

вҺ•CC B returns all characters of character class(es) B. If B is an
integer scalar then the result is a character vector, If B is an integer
vector then the result is a nested vector of integer vectors, with one
item per character class.

           вҚқ character class 1: digits (old вҺ•D)
           вҚқ
           вҺ•CC 1
     0123456789

           вҚқ character class 2: uppercase letters A..Z (old вҺ•A)
     ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ

           вҚқ character class 3: lowercase letters a..z
     abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz

           ...

           вҚқ Line drawing characters
           вҺ•CC 7
     в”Ңв”Җв”¬в”Җв”җв•’в•җв•Өв•җв••
     в”ңв”Җв”јв”Җв”Өв•һв•җв•Әв•җв•Ў
     в””в”Җв”ҙв”Җв”ҳв•ҳв•җв•§в•җв•ӣ
     в•“в”Җв•Ҙв”Җв•–в•”в•җв•Ұв•җв•—
     в•ҹв”Җв•«в”Җв•ўв• в•җв•¬в•җв•Ј
     в•ҷв”Җв•Ёв”Җв•ңв•ҡв•җв•©в•җв•қ

           вҚқ Some mathematical symbols
           вҺ•CC 8
     вҺІвҺӣвҺһвҺЎвҺӨвҺ§вҺ«
     вҺівҺңвҺҹвҺўвҺҘвҺЁвҺ¬
     вҶ”вҺқвҺ вҺЈвҺҰвҺ®вҺ®
     в„•в„Өв„ҡв„қв„ӮвҺ©вҺӯ

   A special case is вҺ•CC вҚ¬ (or вҺ•CC вҚі0: it prints the available character
classes for вҺ•CC:

           вҺ•CC вҚ¬
           вҺ•CC   1:  digits 0-9 (same as вҺ•CC 10)
           вҺ•CC   2:  uppercase characters A-Z (same as вҺ•CC 26)
           вҺ•CC   3:  lowercase characters a-z (same as вҺ•CC ВҜ26)
           вҺ•CC   4:  ASCII characters (same as вҺ•CC 127)
           вҺ•CC   5:  superscripts ( ВІВіВ№КІбөҸбөҗбө—вҒ°вҒұвҒҙвҒөвҒ¶вҒ·вҒёвҒ№вҒәвҒ»вҒјвҒҪвҒҫвҒҝ )
           вҺ•CC   6:  subscripts ( бөўвӮҖвӮҒвӮӮвӮғвӮ„вӮ…вӮҶвӮҮвӮҲвӮүвӮҠвӮӢвӮҢвӮҚвӮҺвӮ–вӮҳвӮҷвұј )
           вҺ•CC   7:  line drawing chatacters
           вҺ•CC   8:  octal digits 0-7
           вҺ•CC   9:  some mathematical symbols
           вҺ•CC  10:  decimal digits 0-9
           вҺ•CC  16:  UPPERCASE HEXADECIMAL DIGITS 0-9 A-F
           вҺ•CC ВҜ16:  lowercase hexadecimal digits 0-9 A-F a-f
           вҺ•CC  17:  Hexadecimal Digits 0-9 A-F a-f
           вҺ•CC  26:  UPPERCASE CHARACTERS A-Z
           вҺ•CC ВҜ26:  lowercase characters A-Z
           вҺ•CC  33:  base32 encoding (RFC 4648)
           вҺ•CC  48:  greek characters A-О© Оұ-Пү
           вҺ•CC  52:  characters A-Z a-z
           вҺ•CC  65:  base64 encoding (RFC 4648)
           вҺ•CC  95:  printable characters 0x20 ... 0x7E
           вҺ•CC 128:  ASCII characters

   In many cases is the character class number easy to remember because:

   вҖў the character class number is equal to the number of characters in
     the class, e.g.  26 for A-Z, 52 for A-Z and a-z,
   вҖў negative numbers are the lowercase variants of the uppercase class,
     e.g.  26 for A-Z and ВҜ26 for a-z, and
   вҖў 2*class is the mixed case of the uppercase class.


