2.30 вҺ•FIO - File I/O Functions
==============================

As of GNU APL 1.6, the native function FILE_IO has been replaced by the
system function вҺ•FIO. вҺ•FIO normally takes a numeric axis argument which
selects one of many different functions, most of which are contained in
the standard C library.  The arguments for these functions are usually
the same as the corresponding C functions and the man page for each
function describes the meaning of the arguments.

   For example, вҺ•FIO[3] corresponds to fopen() and вҖҷman fopenвҖҷ explains
what fopen does (opening a file).

   Calling вҺ•FIO monadically without an axis and with an empty right
argument shows a list of all functions provided by вҺ•FIO:

           вҺ•FIO ''
        Functions provided by вҺ•FIO...

        Legend: a - address family, IPv4 address, port (or errno)
                d - table of dirent structs
                e - error code (integer as per errno.h)
                h - file handle (integer)
                i - integer
                n - names (nested vector of strings)
                s - string
                u - time divisor: 1       - second
                                  1000    - milli second
                                  1000000 - micro second
                y4 - seconds, wday, yday, dst (
