2.35 вҺ•MX - Matrix/Statistics
============================

вҺ•MX was kindly contributed by Henrik Moller

   вҺ•MX[x] is a system function that provides a collection of matrix and
statistical operations such as covariance, eigensystems, and so on,
along with random number generation in several statistical
distributions.  Particular operations are selected through the use of
the axis specifier x:

                 вҺ•MX[1] B       (monadic) Determinant
             (A) вҺ•MX[2] B       (nomadic) Cross product
               A вҺ•MX[3] B       (dyadic)  Vector angle
                 вҺ•MX[4] B       (monadic) Eigenvector
                 вҺ•MX[5] B       (monadic) Eigenvalue
                 вҺ•MX[6] B       (monadic) Ident
                 вҺ•MX[7] B       (monadic) Rotation matrix
               A вҺ•MX[8] B       (dyadic)  Homogeneous transform
                 вҺ•MX[9] B       (monadic) Norm
             (A) вҺ•MX[10] B      (nomadic) Randoms
             (A) вҺ•MX[11] B      (nomadic) Covariance
               A вҺ•MX[12] B      (dyadic)  Histogram
               A вҺ•MX[13] B      (dyadic)  Print
                 вҺ•MX[14] B      (monadic) Set RNG seed

   (These may by shown by entering вҺ•MX вҖқ or вҺ•MX[0]0 on the APL command
line.)  In the function list above, A indicates a mandatory left
argument, while (A) indicates an optional left argument.  The right
argument B of вҺ•MX[X] is always mandatory.

