2.36.3 Plot Window Handling
---------------------------

Each call of вҺ•PLOT with some plot data B opens a separate window in the
X server (which implies that вҺ•PLOT requires X). That window runs in its
own thread until it is closed.  A plot window can be closed in different
ways:

   вҖў interactively by clicking on the close button (often located near
     the top-right corner) of the plot window,
   вҖў interactively by opening the drop down menu (if any) of the window
     (near the top left-of the window) and selecting the menu option
     named Close,
   вҖў programmatically from APL by calling вҺ•PLOT ВҜ3 (which closes all
     open plot windows), or
   вҖў programmatically from APL by calling вҺ•PLOT H (which closes a
     specific plot window), where H is the plot window handle returned
     by monadic вҺ•PLOT B, or by dyadic A вҺ•PLOT B with plot attributes A
     and plot data B.

   Note that the exact method for closing a plot window interactively
with the mouse or the keyboard (as opposed to programmatically with
вҺ•PLOT ВҜ3 or вҺ•PLOT H from APL) differs between different window managers.
The above corresponds to the typical method(s) for closing windows on
most systems.


