2.37.2 Monadic вҺ•PNG
-------------------

Monadic вҺ•PNG, i.e.  вҺ•PNG B is used for 3 purposes:

  1. Conversion of PNG files into the GNU APL color model,
  2. Display of an APL array (in the GNU APL color model) in a window on
     the screen (interactive use of PNG), and
  3. Controlling of вҺ•PNG itself.

   The desired purpose is dictated by the properties of *B*:

  1. Any APL text vector (i.e.  a string) *B* is taken as the name of a
     file that supposedly contains an image in the PNG format.  вҺ•PNG
     will read the file and return the pixels in it as a numeric APL
     array of rank 3.  The array contains the color components of the
     image in the file as described above.
  2. Any array *B* with rank 3 must be numeric (with values from 0.0 to
     1.0) and is then assumed to be an array in the GNU APL color model
     (such as the result of the case above).  This image is displayed in
     a new window on the screen; the window survives even after вҺ•PNG has
     returned.  The result returned by вҺ•PNG is a window handle (a
     positive integer identifying the window) which may later be used
     (in the case described below) to close the window programmatically
     from APL. Alternatively the window can also be closed interactively
     by the user via its close button.
  3. Finally, if *B* is a numeric scalar it fine-tunes the вҺ•PNG
     behaviour:

        вҖў вҺ•PNG N with N вүҘ 1 (as returned in the case above) closes the
          window with handle N programmatically.

        вҖў вҺ•PNG 0 disables all debug printouts related to вҺ•PNG.
        вҖў вҺ•PNG ВҜ1 turns on a debug printout related to вҺ•PNG (X events).
        вҖў вҺ•PNG ВҜ2 turns on a debug printout related to вҺ•PNG (image
          data).
        вҖў вҺ•PNG ВҜ3 closes all open вҺ•PNG windows.
        вҖў вҺ•PNG ВҜ4 turns on a debug printout related to вҺ•PNG (GTK
          drawing).
        вҖў вҺ•PNG ВҜ5 turns on a debug printout related to вҺ•PNG (function
          calls).
        вҖў вҺ•PNG ВҜ6 returns a vector of all open вҺ•PNG window handles.


File: apl.info,  Node: Dyadic вҺ•PNG,  Next: APL Examples,  Prev: Monadic вҺ•PNG,  Up: вҺ•PNG - Portable Network Graphics

2.37.3 Dyadic вҺ•PNG
------------------

Dyadic *A вҺ•PNG B* has only one purpose: to store an APL array in the GNU
APL color model into a PNG file.

   вҖў If *A* is a text vector then it is taken as the name of a PNG file
     into which the image *B* shall be written.  In this case the
     resolution is 8 bits for each color component.
   вҖў If *A* is a 2-element vector, say *(A1 A2) вҶҗ A*, then the nested
     *A1* is the name of a PNG file as before and *A2* is the resolution
     (1, 2, 4, 8, or 16) to be used for the output file.  In this case
     the combination of the general image format (as implied by *вҶ‘вҚҙB*)
     and resolution *A2* must be a valid one in the PNG standard.


