2.41 вҺ•SI - State Indicator
==========================

вҺ•SI returns aspects of the current State Indicator, similar to the
standard command )SI. This can be used, for example, to create debug
functions similar to the assert() macro in C/C++:

     вҲҮAssert B;COND;LOC;VAR
      вҶ’(1вүЎB)вҚҙ0
      ' '
      CONDвҶҗ7вҶ“,ВҜ2 вҺ•SI 4
      LOCвҶҗ,ВҜ2 вҺ•SI 3
      '************************************************'
      ' '
      '*** Assertion (', COND, ') failed at ',LOC
      ''

      вҚқ show stack
      вҚқ
      ' '
      'Stack:'
      7 вҺ•CR вҠғВҜ1вҶ“вҺ•SI 3
      ' '
      '************************************************</pre>'
      вҶ’
     вҲҮ

   The right argument of вҺ•SI specifies which aspect of the State
Indicator shall be returned:

   вҖў вҺ•SI 1: The name of the context.  That name is either:
        вҖў the name of a defined function, or
        вҖў в—Ҡ for an immediate execution context, or
        вҖў вҚҺ for an execute context.

   вҖў вҺ•SI 2: The line number (of a defined function) or 0 for immediate
     execution and execute contexts.

   вҖў вҺ•SI 3: The function name and line number in square brackets, for
     example: "FOO[3]"

   вҖў вҺ•SI 4: Either the statement text of the function line or the error
     text of an error that has occurred on the line

   вҖў вҺ•SI 5: The program counter (= token number counted from the start
     of the function text)

   вҖў вҺ•SI 6: the parse mode of the context (immediate execution, execute,
     or defined function).

   If no left argument is provided then the result of вҺ•SI is a vector
with one entry per State Indicator level (and hence вҚҙвҺ•SI B is the depth
of the SI stack).

   If the optional left argument A is provided then it specifies a
particular level of the SI instead of the entire SI. A should be an
integer scalar.  If A is positive then the level is counted from the
oldest entry to the latest, while negative A counts from the latest to
the oldest level.

   For example, ВҜ1 вҺ•SI refers to the currently executing context, ВҜ2 вҺ•SI
is the caller, and so on.


