2.42.2 вҺ•SQL[0] вҖҳ''вҖҷ : display sub-function names
------------------------------------------------

As of SVN version 1901, вҺ•SQL has been promoted to be a function group.
Instead of the function nunbers above, one can therefore also use
function names with the following syntax:

         With a small performance penalty, вҺ•SQL also accepts the following
         sub-function names instead of sub-function numbers as axis argument:

         Legend: Fs - database file name (path)
                 Ty - database type ('sqlite' or 'postgres')
                 Db - database handle (small integer)
                 Qs - SQL query string
                 Pv - query parameters (APL values, to be bound to Qs)
                 Ts - name of a table in the database (string)
                 Vi - DB provider (library) version (integer)
                 Vs - DB provider (library) version (string)

            вҺ•SQL[5]         вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.begin         вҚқ begin a transaction
            вҺ•SQL[9]         вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.columns       вҚқ show the columns of a table
            вҺ•SQL[6]         вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.commit        вҚқ end a transaction
            вҺ•SQL[2]         вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.close         вҚқ close a database handle
            вҺ•SQL[0]         вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.list ''       вҚқ вҺ•SQL function names/numbers
            вҺ•SQL[1] Fs      вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.open          вҚқ open the database file
            вҺ•SQL[3, Db] Pv  вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.query Db Pv   вҚқ SQL database query
            вҺ•SQL[7] Db      вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.rollback      вҚқ roll a transaction back
            вҺ•SQL[8] Db      вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.tables        вҚқ show all tables
         Qs вҺ•SQL[4, Db] Pv  вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.update Db Pv  вҚқ SQL database update
            вҺ•SQL[10]        вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.version       вҚқ SQL provider version number
            вҺ•SQL[11]        вҶҗвҶ’  вҺ•SQL.vstring       вҚқ SQL provider version string

   NOTE: The mapping from function numbers to function names of a
function group does not allow for non-scalar axis arguments (such as [3,
Db]) for query or [4, Db] for update.  For that reason, the Db argument
of functions query and update had to be moved from the second item in
the axis argument to the first item of the right value argument, and the
right argument Pv (aka.  query parameters) of the function axis is now
the (nested) second argument of the right argument in the named function
symtax.

   Like for вҺ•SQL[0] вҚ¬ above is the axis argument [0] optional; one can
therefore also use вҺ•SQL вҖқ instead of вҺ•SQL[0] вҖқ.


