2.44.4 Monadic вҺ•XML
-------------------

Z вҶҗ вҺ•XML B converts APL string B that contains a valid XML document to
an associative APL array Z and vice versa.

   Note: If you convert an associative APL array back to a an XML
document, the result is a possibly very long string containing several
linefeed characters.  That is OK if the string is written to a file, but
causes problems when the string is displayed and longer than вҺ•PW. The
standard APL folding of output near вҺ•PW make the string then look
somewhat garbled.  This effect can be suppressed in 2 ways:

  1. set вҺ•PW large enough, or
  2. prefix the string with вҠғ35вҺ•CR as in the examples below.


