2.44.5 Dyadic вҺ•XML
------------------

Z вҶҗ A вҺ•XML B provides a number of convenience functions.  Its left
argument A is an integer function number, possibly followed by arguments
of the function number вҶ‘A.

   In the following examples, let

           XMLвҶҗ36 вҺ•CR """
     <?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
       <Document>
         <Tag1 name='tag1'>   <!-- first tag -->
           TEXT1
           <Subtag name='subag1.1'>   <!-- first subtag -->
             SUBTEXT1_1
           </Subtag>
         </Tag1>
       </Document>
     """

     APLвҶҗвҺ•XML XML

   Then

   вҖў ZвҶҗ0 вҺ•XML B is the same as monadic ZвҶҗвҺ•XML B.

   вҖў ZвҶҗ1 вҺ•XML B is like 0 вҺ•XML B, except that B is not the XML document
     (string) itself but the name of a file from which an XML document
     is read.

   вҖў ZвҶҗ2 вҺ•XML B splits an APL member path (a sequence of member names)
     into a vector P of (nested) member names.  This vector P is
     understood by the APL primitive PICK (i.e.  ZвҶҗPвҠғAPL or
     (PвҠғAPL)вҶҗvalue and can be used to address the data in an XML node.

   вҖў ZвҶҗ3 вҺ•XML B splits an APL member name (as produced by e.g.  monadic
     вҺ•XML into a 3-item vector Z. Z[1] is a single character indicating
     the category (i.e.  a character scalar вҲҶ, вҚҷ, or _).  Z[2] is the
     position (an integer scalar вүҘ вҺ•IO). Z[3] is a (nested) APL string.
     3 вҺ•XML has an inverse function ВҜ3 вҺ•XML which converts a 3-item
     vector as produced by 3 вҺ•XML back into an APL member name
     indicating the category (i.e.  _, вҲҶ, or вҚҷ) and the name from the
     XML tag:

                      8 вҺ•CR (C P N)вҶҗ3 вҺ•XML "вҲҶ2comment"
          в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
          в”ӮвҲҶ 2 в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җв”Ӯ
          в”Ӯ    в”Ӯcommentв”Ӯв”Ӯ
          в”Ӯ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳв”Ӯ
          в””вҲҠв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ

                C   вҚқ category
          вҲҶ
                P   вҚқ position
          2
                N   вҚқ (XML-) name
          comment

                ВҜ3 вҺ•XML C P N   вҚқ inverse of 3 вҺ•XML
          вҲҶ2comment

   вҖў ZвҶҗ4 вҺ•XML B is a string that shows the member names of the
     associative array B in a tree-like fashion.  For example:

                вҠғ35вҺ•CR 4 вҺ•XML APL
